- Many op kernels use the To32Bit() function, which does not do any
  bounds checking and can cause silent corruption due to int32
  overflow.
  E.g., tf.zeros/ones/fill silently give incorrect results when the
  number of elements is >= 2**31.
- This commit adds a new helper function MaybeWith32BitIndexing() that
  checks the indexing bounds and converts tensors to 32-bit only if
  it is safe to do so (and only for GPU devices). This fixes the
  cases that were previously broken, and simplifies the ones that
  already had explicit bounds checks.","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/99002d4a4336e2c5a9d6fd64e64dda5325af0827"},{"sha":"dba2a5db51ee95efd79c96d18f72d962d7d8bfbd","author":{"name":"Ben Barsdell","email":"fb55efc015c19b6b983311e9fae7c0ecda2e4774@nvidia.com"},"message":"Simplify code in MaybeWith32BitIndexingImpl","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/dba2a5db51ee95efd79c96d18f72d962d7d8bfbd"},{"sha":"2cf981016f64a4d185b31958403020f13a730698","author":{"name":"Ben Barsdell","email":"fb55efc015c19b6b983311e9fae7c0ecda2e4774@nvidia.com"},"message":"Add workaround for when num_bits=0 in GpuRadixSort

Previously, resource alias analysis effectively only worked for one island
because island return resource values were marked as "unknown". Now, values are
propagated from within the island such that cross-island analysis works as
expected. This means that the analysis can now also be used after
`BreakUpIsland` pass has run.

[{"sha":"b29c44dd920567b2ec121f5c64f2aed3f1263b7b","author":{"name":"Jaesung Chung","email":"935e11c5b050a3a02c4f0e08de55daf431709deb@google.com"},"message":"Disable lowering static tensor lists when the batch size is None by default

Converter forces to use the size one when the given batch size is None during
lowering tensor list ops. This assumption often fails and users consistently
report the bugs from internal/external users. It would be nice to disable the
problematic assumption by default and enable it safely when users aware of the
option.

All the existing clients, who are using the default size to batch one, have
enabled the
'converter._experimental_default_to_batch_one_in_tensor_list_ops = True`
explicitly. So, we can disable the option safely.
